farmer_mack,"Dec 27, 2018","Seems to be good quality. It was easy to set up once I got my head wrapped around the set-up concepts.

It is installed and ready for use but in my application it has not yet been ""used.""  I want it to control an engine block heater in my truck. It is set to trigger ON when the outdoor temperature dips to 15°F or below, and trigger OFF when the outdoor temperature rises to  20°F or above.  Set point is 20° and the heat differential is 5°. So it will trigger on at PV - HD (Process value or set point less Heating Differential or lower, then back OFF at PV or above. This will prevent rapid cycling as the outdoor temperature fluctuates. The heater cord is plugged into the ""Heating"" receptacle while the ""cooling"" receptacle is unused.  Since being deployed the outdoor temperature has not 
Read full review"
edbeltran2000,"Nov 24, 2020","So there is no plug and play here.  All goes well until you realize that if your router does not automatically work in 2.4mhz or has the capability of doing 2.4mhz this will not work.  So if router only does 5.0 u are toast.   So now there is a bit of configuration that has to be done to get 2.4 set up for it to communicate in/out to the App.  
Am waiting until the weekend when I have time to mess with it and hope it works out.  If not returning.  Otherwise it’s just a really expensive yet accurate thermometer.   "
ronduck1,"Oct 02, 2018","Very reasonably priced.  Lighter than the old, other brand product I used for five years. Way less costly.  Digital instead of dial knob temp control. Easy to mount on the wall by my kegerator.  Works like a charm keeping my modified chest freezer cycling on and off to keep my beer at 35-40 degrees.  It displays current temp in the kegerator and the temp I've set it to keep.  When the temp in the kegerator climbs 3 degrees about the set temperature, it turns on the chest freezer to cool it down again.  Works great."
tradition111,"Jan 24, 2017","Easy to setup, easy to use, easy to monitor. Great value compared to other similar equipment. Not sure why this is not more common, seems like the Johnson Controls solution is too exspensive and complicated. "
sonjamayo,"Sep 30, 2020",works great once you can get it set....which admittedly was a bit difficult for me ....and yes I read the instructions. After following the instructions and getting to the end you have to hold the button for a few seconds. I didn't see that in the instructions and accordingly i thought the first one was malfunctioning so bought another and when it had issues I knew I had been missing something. That one step was missed...ugh!
dsmtoys,"Aug 04, 2017","The product is made from solid materials with a large and bright readout display.  Once you read the instructions, which you have to do, and set the temperature on-off parameters the first time, it is straight-forward after that.  The temperature probe has a 5 foot lead which worked fine for my application.  I use it to control fans on a rack server entertainment system.  It exceeded my expectations on quality and function.  I would buy it again without hesitation."
dpecchio,"Nov 14, 2017","Arrived very quickly.  The instructions were easy to follow, however, skip to the part to choose units ""C or F"" first.  Then run through the rest of the programming.  Worked so well I ordered a second for my other reef tank."
fairdee2012,"Jan 15, 2020",Had this a little over a year. It worked fine within a first few months then it over- heated my tank  a couple times. Th he alarm worked a few times but then I couldn’t get it to turn without having to unplugged it.Now I cant get the temp set without the alarm going offeven though the water temp is below the parameters.Currently not using at all. 
heat1895david,"Aug 10, 2017",I used this on my hot water solar panel with an electric valve. It works great. It shuts off the solar panel if it gets to cool. Keeps my swimming pool nice and warm..
wwalters,"Jan 09, 2017","I brought this item to control my cheese cave (mini refigerator).
it worked great. Then I needed it in an refigerator that I store apples in, the problem was the they would get to cold and freeze when the outside temperture got to cold.
so I pluged the refig into the cold side and placed a trouble light into the heat side of the Inkbird, set the temp to 35°f set the differ of 2°F and the apples stay cold and crisp!  So I needed another for the cheesd cave.
I highly recommend the unit."
travnat12,"Feb 18, 2017","Its easy to use once you understand the 2 letter symbols and what they're for.  I have 2 of these now, one for beer brewing and one to replace a broken thermostat on a really old deep freezer."
su9476,"Sep 15, 2024","I purchased one last year to install into Generac oil heating circuit. I made the mistake of putting it inside the cabinet and after a 50 + hour run this summer, I found it didn't do well from the engine heat. I'm installing this one outside the cabinet inside an electrical connection box with gasketed lid. Should last for years. Very easy to set up, calibrate, and operate. set it and forget it."
dodgecrazyandy383,"Nov 03, 2020","I’m very happy with this controller, keeps my Sulcata tortoise house at a constant temperature. Easy to program and I also like the large temperature display."
