johnat250,"Dec 22, 2021","It is hard to imagine a better bargain for process control.  I have been using PID controllers for years and for most applications, you don't need proportional control. My typical PID with SSR control costs about $300. 

This is a less sophisticated controller and is a typical bang-bang controller. The control is referenced for cooling which means if you want to turn on a heater you set the heater turn off temperature in the set point and the heater turn on point in the hysteresis band. For example, I am using this for my green house where I turn on lights to keep the plants warm. The set point is 42F. At temperatures above 42, the heater is off. The hysteresis band is 2 degrees. Therefore, the lights turn on at 40F. 

The quality is very good too.  For home projects like greenRead full review"
