retiredpaul5,"Dec 22, 2020","All of these floating thermometers suffer from the same problem. They are inaccurate at the thermometer itself without any user way to adjust/calibrate them. Ones I had purchased in the past were 6 degrees off and were sent back. The one I purchased is 3 degrees too high, but I will live with it. Else the radio function seems to work well where other don't."
m63ku,"Jun 11, 2019","I’ve had a few of these for brewing and for a saltwater fish tank. They hold the temperature reasonably well, but tend to fail suddenly. This may be due to the harsh conditions near the aquarium (lots of salt in the air), but I can’t recommend for long term or critical use."
ma9035_blgc08,"Dec 24, 2019",Used to convert a 14cu ft upright freezer into a no freezer refrigerator. for off gridd. Highly recommended for this use. Power use is just 14 watts per hour. Easy to program. Has a compressor delay option. I can read the display from across the room. I have bins on all the shelves to keep cold air in better when opening. Dont hesitate to get one of these.
